article.description: Trae Bell-Haynes scored 21 points, Ethan O'Day had 19 and Vermont kept Quinnipiac at bay for an 83-70 win Wednesday night.
article.headline: Vermont beats Quinnipiac 83-70 on strength of Bell-Haynes
article.linkText: Vermont beats Quinnipiac 83-70 on strength of Bell-Haynes
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Trae Bell-Haynes scored 21 points, Ethan O'Day had 19 and Vermont kept Quinnipiac at bay for an 83-70 win Wednesday night. Vermont (1-2) used a 10-2 first-half run to make the score 33-23. Quinnipiac (0-2) later cut the deficit to five -- 41-36 and 54-49 -- but could get no closer. The Catamounts shot 58.3 percent to 38.2 for Quinnipiac. Giovanni McLean led the Bobcats with 18 points shooting 6 for 15 from the floor. He was 4 for 8 from 3-point range. Nate Rohrer's dunk with 2:02 left gave Vermont its biggest lead to make it 77-60. Quinnipiac had won three of its last four games against the Catamounts entering the game. Last year it handed Vermont its worst defeat of the season with an 89-73 win. Vermont now owns a 7-3 series advantage against the Bobcats.
